turns.speaker: M
turns.content: We were very much younger then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And very much sillier.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: However I believe the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh.  You knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort.  You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents?  It was only a trivial, little brooch.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It was bristling with diamonds.  In the worst possible taste, too.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It was not.  I still have it, and I wear it often.  It is very pretty.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I did not.  You worked that whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, you let him kiss you, huh?  You said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, what of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It gave him a lot of pleasure and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: If you hadn't been so suspicious and nosey, you never would have known a thing about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a nice point of view, I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh dear.  I'm bored with this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So am I.  I'm bored stiff. [GARBAGE]  Do you want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No.  Thank you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have a little, I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't know why you'd want any, you've already had three glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason.  Anyhow, they are very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I just think it's silly to go on and on and on about such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly call three glasses of liquor a whole evening long, going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's become a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh.  Don't be so grand.  Just because you don't happen to want one at the moment.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: you going out somewhere, dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No.  I am just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh.  It's a woman's duty to allure the man.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well as a matter of fact, yes, that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh really.  It's a pity you didn't have any brandy, it would have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's funny it hasn't worked such wonders for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Snap, snap, snap.  You know you are like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nonsense.  They have a bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap. They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting. I don't care.  Do you understand?  I don't care if they bark and they roll about like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes I did, quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And I suppose you let him kiss you a good deal more than, too. Yes.  I suppose you guys had a riotous time, huh?  All out, no restraint at all.  Well, you never really had much anyhow.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your own business.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable, I expect it's because you are drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I am not in the least bit drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I mentioned once before that I've had three minute liquor glasses the whole evening long.  A child of two cannot get drunk on that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On the contrary, a child of two can get violently drunk on only one glass of brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's very interesting Amanda. How about a child of four?  Or a child of six?  Or a child of nine? We can get a good little conversation going on about this, you know, intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh shut up.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Shut up.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny, darling.  Why don't you have some more brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: [LAUGHTER] That's a very good idea.  I think I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look, you better turn that off. I don't want to wake up the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There are no people upstairs; it's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well then you'll wake up the people downstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They are away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time of year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I will do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Fine if you insist on being boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Will you turn that off, it's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are far too temperamental, try to control yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I won't.  Let go, let go of me. Listen, listen?  I'm sick and tired of listening to you, you sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda, listen, listen.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh.  That's very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh shut up.  Let go.  I hate you, I hate you.  Do you hear?  You are a conceited and overbearing and utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You are a vile, ill-tempered, loose living, wicked little beast and I never want to see you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end.  Do you hear me?  Finally and forever.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not going like this.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh.  Yes I am.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes I am.   Stop it. Stop it.  Let go of me. Oh.  You're a cruel fiend.  I loathe and I hate you. Marry you again?  Never, never, never. I hope you die in torment, you brute beast cad.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up. Shut up. God, I wouldn't marry you again if you came crawling back to me on a bended knee.  You are a vile, ill-tempered, mean little wench and I never want to see you again as long as I live.
